<activity xml:id="class_baseball-bat-1">
	<title>The Baseball Bat I</title>
<introduction>
<p></p>
    <p>
      A futuristic model for a baseball bat of mass <m>M</m> is the triangle shown below. The bat has length <m>L</m> and its widest width is <m>W</m>. You want to find the bat's center of mass.
    </p>
	<figure xml:id="fig_rot-bat1">
			<title>Ring Figure</title>
			<caption>A simplified two-dimensional model for a baseball bat.</caption>
			<image source="bat1.png" width = "50%">
				<description></description>
			</image>
		</figure>
	</introduction>
	<task>
		<statement>
			<p>
				Draw a picture. What origin do you want to choose?
				
			</p>
		</statement>
	</task>
	<task>
		<statement>
			<p>
				<alert>Chop:</alert> How would you chop the baseball bat into small pieces? Draw a diagram showing the small pieces and label <m>dm</m>, <m>dA</m>, and <m>r</m>.  Find the mass of one of the small pieces you drew.
			</p>
		</statement>
	</task>
	<task>
		<statement>
			<p>
				<alert>Multiply:</alert> Using the results from the previous steps, multiply the components together to get your infinitesimal <m>d\vec{r}_{cm}</m>.
			</p>
		</statement>
	</task>
	<task>
		<statement>
			<p>
				<alert>Add:</alert> Compute the integral for the center of mass.
			</p>
		</statement>
	</task>
</activity>

